info.name: CISC3140 Lab 4
info.description: CIS3140 Lab 4 is a `<Node/Express API>` that uses SQL and JavaScript to enable users to view and update data about cars. The API can be viewed here: [cisc3140lab4.herokuapp.com](cisc3140lab4.herokuapp.com).

request.description:
API endpoint to get *All Cars* in the system database.
> A successful request will result in a *HTTP 200* Status code.

response.name: All Cars

request.description:
API endpoint to get *Car by ID* in the system database.
> A successful request will result in a *HTTP 200* Status code.

API endpoint to get a *Car by Make* in the system database.
> A successful request will result in a *HTTP 200* Status code.

API endpoint to create a new *Car* in the system database.
> A successful request will result in a *HTTP 200* Status code.

An entry successfully created will be visible on `</api/cars>`.

If the created entry has an email or ID that's already in the system database it will not be created.
> An unsuccessful request will result in a *HTTP 400* Status code.

API endpoint to update information on an existing *Car* in the system database.
> A successful request will result in a *HTTP 200* Status code.

An entry successfully updated will be visible on `</api/cars>`.

Users can edit all possible keys for each entry in the database, including the keys responsible for housing car judged by categories, such as `"racer_turbo"` or `"mods_overall"`, etc. In the example below, we updated the `"engine_chrome"` key with a value of 3.
